[normal]NAPIT stance of Qualified Supervisor model[bold]&#xa0;[bold]NAPIT’s scheme is based on the person who 
[normal]attends site to 
[normal]inspect and test the installation being a Qualified Operative who is at least equiva
[normal]lent to the EAS Qualified Supervisor. Because we have a high proportion of micro
[normal]‐
[normal]business this is still often one person.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The total number of Qualified Operatives is 12
[normal],
[normal]235 within 9006 enterprises. 8134 operatives work for 8134 sole traders and micro
[normal]‐
[normal]companies (i.e. 1 per enterprise) and 4101 operatives work for 872 larger companies at an average of 4.7 per enterprise (excluding one very large scheme member gives an average of 3.2 qualified operatives per enterprise for the rest).
